#AD / Whole Foods Market’s Annual Beauty Week Event is coming up, and each year they highlight their Top 5 Beauty Trends…

This year’s trends include 2 that I’m enjoying: jelly textures that feel refreshing yet moisturizing, such as in the Mad Hippie Jelly Cleanser, and ceramides such as in the ACURE Ultra Hydrating Plant Ceramide Daily Facial lotion, that help support the skin barrier. 

This year’s trends also include products with prickly pear, overnight hair products such as silk scrunchies, and SPFs that aren’t thick and pasty, which is not just a trend for this year, but for every year.

latestPosts.caption:
Updated tutorial for my signature smoky winged eyeliner and 2 ways to do it

It's subtly elongating and opens my eyes up a little bit, and is so so easy to do because it's so forgiving. 

You'll need 3 things:
1. Pencil eyeliner - I'm using @maccosmetics teddy here but any favorite eyeliner works
2. @rephr.to pencil 03 brush - you can use any pencil brush but the rephr is my favorite
3. Powder eyeshadow - I'm using Mac Brun

And this can be created with any color eyeliner too

Some of this will be trial and error depending on your eyeshape but this is what I find works best:

1. Tilt your head up and look down into a mirror 
2. Use your eyeliner to draw a line extending from the angle of your lower lash line straight out. Start small because you can always drag it out longer with the brush+ eyeshadow.
3. Connect that line to your lash line and keep the connection as thin as possible- I find for me that going NO FARTHER than 1/3 into my eyeliner is the best length for me

If it's not a perfect line, if it's not even, not as far out as you want, don't worry! Here's where the blending comes in:

4. OPTION 1 - Blend with a clean pencil brush with no eyeshadow for a more soft look
5. OPTION 2 - use your powder eyeshadow to drag out the line a little more, fill in any unevenness, and set the eyeliner - this is my preferred method to keep the eyeliner on all day

Thats it! It takes some trial and error but once you do it a few times it becomes so easy

Let me know if you try this ❤️

#eyelinertutorial #wingedeyeliber #makeuptutorial

Eyeliner tutorial. Smoky winged eyeliner. Makeup tutorial. Signature look. Signature makeup look. Easy makeup. How to do winged eyeliner. Soft glam makeup.

How I do my liner everyday - and it's way easier than it looks. 

Draw a rough line with your color of choice - I like a deep brown, and then blend it out into a wing using eyeshadow

This creates a softer Smokey look that still adds definition.

I'm using @sisleyparisofficial Phyto-Kohl Star Waterproof liners in 2 Tonka (pr) blended out with the deep brown in @welovecoco Clair obscure quad. I use the @rephr.to 03 pencil brush to blend out -I own two of these brushes and they're my favorite to blend out my eyeliners.

I rotate through 5 or 6 different liners and eyeshadows so you can use any liner and shadow combo you want.

Have more questions? Ask away!

Ps a full face grwm reel with this look is coming soon 😉

#eyeliner #wingedliner #eyelinertutorial #easyeyeliner #cateye #makeuptutorial #easymakeup #easymakeuptutorial #viralmakeup #smokeyeye #Asianmakeup #asianeyemakeup #makeuplover #sisleyparis #rephr #chanelbeauty #welovecoco

The lip stain formula I've been looking for...

The @violette_fr lip nectars hit all of my preferences in a lip stain formula - lightweight, hydrating, natural looking, and longwearing 

The formula has an almost jelly feel so they adhere to my lips in a nourishing coat rather than immediately sinking into lip lines like many stain formulas - the shine wears off gracefully into a sheer stain that looks so natural but gives a little hint of color 

It isn't drying at all throughout the day, even on drier lip says and I find the stain to last 5-6 hours after the shine has worn off

The shades are also perfect and I've been rotating through all of them:
Betise - classic rosy berry and the perfect red tint
Dahlia noir - deep plum berry, and great for a deeper tint
Rose de Moab - light caramel tint and super natural
Pois de Senteur - rosy pink tint 

Which one is your favorite?
